## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.8+
- pip

### Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/19aron98/Wind-Farm-Layout-Optimization.git
cd Wind-Farm-Layout-Optimization

python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate        # Linux/macOS
# .venv\Scripts\activate         # Windows

pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Dependencies

```text
numpy
pandas
matplotlib
scipy
scikit-learn
xgboost
seaborn
jupyter
pyyaml
pytest
```

---

## Usage

### Baseline optimization (current notebook)

```bash
jupyter notebook WindFarmOptimization.ipynb
```

Steps inside the notebook:

1. Load `wind_speed_map.csv`
2. Initialize random turbine positions
3. Run gradient descent with penalty-based constraints
4. Visualize initial vs optimized layout

### Planned hybrid pipeline

```bash
# Generate labeled training data
python -m wind_farm_opt.ml.dataset --samples 10000 --output data/layouts.csv

# Train XGBoost surrogate
python -m wind_farm_opt.ml.surrogate --train data/layouts.csv --model models/aep_surrogate.json

# Run hybrid optimization
python -m wind_farm_opt.optimize \
  --turbines 30 \
  --solver slsqp \
  --surrogate models/aep_surrogate.json \
  --top-k 20 \
  --seed 42

# Benchmark solvers
python -m wind_farm_opt.evaluation.benchmark --config configs/experiment.yaml
```

---

## Evaluation & Benchmarks

The project compares multiple approaches on the same wind farm instance:

| Method | What it measures |
|--------|------------------|
| Random baseline | AEP without optimization |
| Penalty gradient descent | Single-run local optimization |
| Multistart L-BFGS-B / SLSQP | Improved local search |
| XGBoost surrogate only | ML prediction without refinement |
| Hybrid ML + physics | Surrogate prefilter + constrained refinement |

**Key metrics:**

- Final AEP (MW)
- AEP improvement over random layout (%)
- Surrogate prediction error (RMSE / MAE)
- Number of full physics evaluations
- Total runtime (seconds)
- Constraint satisfaction (spacing, boundary)

---

## Results

Reported outcomes from the baseline and target hybrid system:

| Metric | Baseline | Target (Hybrid) |
|--------|----------|-----------------|
| AEP improvement vs random init | ~4.3% | ~8–15% with multistart |
| Physics evaluations during search | High (every candidate) | Reduced ~90% with surrogate |
| Final layout feasibility | Penalty-enforced | Hard constraint validation |
| Solver comparison | Single method | Multi-solver benchmark |

Example outputs:

- Initial vs optimized turbine layout on wind speed heatmap
- Convergence curves for objective and constraint violation
- Predicted vs true AEP scatter plot for surrogate validation
- Solver comparison bar chart (AEP, runtime, evaluations)

